@NODE "Arg_Routines" "Arg_Routines"
@{b}Argument Routines @{ub}

	@{"ParseArgs()  " LINK "ParseArgs"}
	@{"DisposeArgs()" LINK "DisposeArgs"}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "ParseArgs" "ParseArgs()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	ParseArgs - easier interface to ReadArgs()@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	ParseArgs(template, args)
		     A0      A1

	@{"FuncArgs" LINK "dopus/args.h/File" 10} *ParseArgs(char *, char *);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	This routine makes it much more straightforward to use ReadArgs() to
	parse an argument string. Using ReadArgs to parse a string requires
	you to allocate and initialise a RDArgs structure and argument
	array structure, and also requires the argument string to have a
	newline character. This function automates this process for you.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	template - pointer to ReadArgs template string
	args - pointer to argument string (need not have a newline)@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
	If successful, this function returns a @{"FuncArgs" LINK "dopus/args.h/File" 10} structure. This
	structure has several fields, but the useful ones are :

	    FA_Arguments

	    This is the argument array you should use. It is an array
	    of long *, each member of which points to the argument result
	    for the corresponding template entry. If you need to modify
	    any of the values in this array you can, as it is just a copy
	    of the real array.

	    FA_Count

	    This contains the number of arguments in the template. Opus
	    counts the arguments in the template and initialises the
	    argument array accordingly.

	The strings supplied to this function are not needed once the
	function has returned.@{b}

    NOTES@{ub}
	You should use this routine when parsing arguments supplied to
	your Opus modules.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"DisposeArgs()" LINK "DisposeArgs"}, dos.library/ReadArgs()

@ENDNODE
@NODE "DisposeArgs" "DisposeArgs()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	DisposeArgs - free a @{"FuncArgs" LINK "dopus/args.h/File" 10} structure@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	DisposeArgs(funcargs)
		       A0

	void DisposeArgs(@{"FuncArgs" LINK "dopus/args.h/File" 10} *);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	This function frees the @{"FuncArgs" LINK "dopus/args.h/File" 10} structure returned by @{"ParseArgs()" LINK "ParseArgs"}.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	funcargs - pointer to @{"FuncArgs" LINK "dopus/args.h/File" 10} structure to free@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
	The structure is free. Once you have freed it, none of the arguments
	remain valid, so you should make local copies of anything you need
	to refer to.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"ParseArgs()" LINK "ParseArgs"}, dos.library/ReadArgs()

@ENDNODE
@NODE "BOOPSI_gadgets" "BOOPSI_gadgets"
@{b}BOOPSI Gadgets@{ub}

@{b}CLASSES@{ub}

	@{"dopusbuttongclass  " LINK "dopusbuttongclass"}	@{"dopuscheckgclass  " LINK "dopuscheckgclass"}
	@{"dopusframeclass    " LINK "dopusframeclass"}	@{"dopusiclass       " LINK "dopusiclass"}
	@{"dopuslistviewgclass" LINK "dopuslistviewgclass"}	@{"dopuspalettegclass" LINK "dopuspalettegclass"}
	@{"dopusstrgclass     " LINK "dopusstrgclass"}	@{"dopusviewgclass   " LINK "dopusviewgclass"}

@{b}PURPOSE@{ub}

    The dopus5.library makes several BOOPSI gadgets available globally.
    These gadgets can be accessed globally without even opening the
    dopus5.library, although it is a good idea to open it to make sure the
    library is present in the system.

	The gadgets are all sub-classes of standard BOOPSI gadgets, and so take
    all the standard tags (GA_Left, GA_Top, etc..). Often they are based heavily
    on GadTools gadgets and will support equivalent GadTools tags. They also
    have their own set of tags, which is described below.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "dopusbuttongclass" "dopusbuttongclass"

@{b}dopusbuttongclass@{ub}

    The dopusbuttongclass provides a standard pushbutton gadget. It is
    similar to a standard buttongclass gadget, but provides some additional
    functionality. This is via the following tags:

	@{"GTCustom_TextAttr" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 295} (struct TextAttr *) (I) - used to specify a font for
	    the gadget label. (default is the window font).

	@{"GTCustom_ThinBorders" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 297} (BOOL) (I) - if set to TRUE, the gadget will be
	    rendered with single-pixel borders (default FALSE).

	@{"GTCustom_Borderless" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 316} (BOOL) (I) - if set to TRUE, the gadget will be
	    rendered with no border (default FALSE).

	@{"GTCustom_Bold" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 306} (BOOL) (I) - is set to TRUE, the gadget label will be
	    rendered in bold (default FALSE).

	@{"GTCustom_Style" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 311} (ULONG) (I) - use this tag to control the text style of
	    the gadget label. Valid flags are FSF_BOLD and FSF_ITALIC
	    (default FSF_NORMAL).

	@{"GTCustom_NoGhost" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 310} (BOOL) (I) - if set to TRUE, the gadget imagery will
	    not 'ghost' when the gadget is disabled (default FALSE).

	@{"GTCustom_TextPlacement" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 309} (WORD) (I) - Lets you select the position of the
	    label relative to the gadget. Valid values are:

		PLACETEXT_IN (default)
		PLACETEXT_LEFT
		PLACETEXT_RIGHT
		PLACETEXT_ABOVE

@ENDNODE
@NODE "dopuscheckgclass" "dopuscheckgclass"

@{b}dopuscheckgclass@{ub}

    The dopuscheckgclass provides a replacement for GadTools checkbox
    gadgets. As a BOOPSI class, it allows you to have a checkbox without
    using GadTools. This class uses the same basic code as the
    dopusbuttongclass, and as such supports the same tags. The class also
    supports the GTCB_Checked flag (defined in libraries/gadtools.h) to set
    or get the current state of the gadget.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "dopusframeclass" "dopusframeclass"

@{b}dopusframeclass@{ub}

    The dopusframeclass is a BOOPSI class for a frame gadget. A frame
    gadget does not respond to user input; its only purpose is to draw a
    frame (usually around some other gadgets). This class uses the same
    basic code as the dopusbuttongclass, and as such supports the same tags.
    The class also supports the @{"GTCustom_FrameFlags" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 312} tag, to specify flags
    for the frame. Currently, the only defined flag is @{"AREAFLAG_RECESSED" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 104},
    which causes the frame to be drawn as recessed.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "dopusiclass" "dopusiclass"

@{b}dopusiclass@{ub}

    This class allows you to access several predefined images. The
    image you receive is controlled by the following tags:

	    @{"DIA_Type" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 330}

	    This sets the image type. Current valid types are:

		@{"IM_ARROW_UP" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 333}	- an up arrow
		@{"IM_ARROW_DOWN" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 334}	- a down arrow
		@{"IM_CHECK" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 335}	- a check mark
		@{"IM_DRAWER" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 336}	- a "folder" image
		@{"IM_BBOX" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 338}		- a filled box with a border
		@{"IM_BORDER_BOX" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 337}	- a filled box
		@{"IM_ICONIFY" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 339}	- an iconify gadget image
		@{"IM_LOCK" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 341}		- a lock gadget image


	    @{"DIA_FrontPen" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 331}

	    This sets the front pen for the image. Currently, only the
	    @{"IM_CHECK" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 335} image supports this tag.

    This class is a sub-class of imageclass, and so supports the
    standard @{"IM_Width" LINK "dopus/images.h/File" 11}, @{"IM_Height" LINK "dopus/images.h/File" 12}, etc, tags. Images are scaled to the
    supplied sizes.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "dopuslistviewgclass" "dopuslistviewgclass"

@{b}dopuslistviewgclass@{ub}

    This boopsi gadget is a replacement for the gadtools LISTVIEW_KIND
    gadgets. It has been designed to "drop-in" as easily as possible, and
    uses many of the same tags as the gadtools equivalent. It is however
    much more flexible than the gadtools gadget.

    The gadget duplicates most of the tags provided by gadtools' listview
    gadget. It also offers some powerful additions not available under
    gadtools. These include :

	o Current selection indicated by highlight bar, checkmark
	  or text colour
	o Multiple-selection of items with checkmarks
	o Items can be rendered in different colours
	o Simple text formatting in the lister
	o Scroller can be optionally removed
	o Supports drag notification
	o Automatic double-click notification
	o Supports resizing via OM_SET

    It also does not suffer from the gadtools problem of resizing itself to an
    integral multiple of the item height (ie, the size you specify is the size
    you get). It is controlled by the following tags:

	@{"DLV_Top" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 358} (WORD) (ISG) - Top item visible in the listview.  This value
	    will be made reasonable if out-of-range (defaults to 0).

	@{"DLV_MakeVisible" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 359} (WORD) (IS) - Number of an item that should be forced
	    within the visible area of the listview by doing minimal scrolling.
	    This tag overrides @{"DLV_Top" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 358}.

	@{"DLV_Labels" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 357} (struct List * or @{"Att_List" LINK "dopus/lists.h/File" 10} *) (ISG) - List of nodes whose
	    ln_Name fields are to be displayed in the listview. Calling
	    SetGadgetAttrs() and specifying 0 will remove the current list.
	    Specifying ~0 will remove the list but will not disturb the display,
	    allowing you to make changes to the contents and selection status.

	@{"DLV_ReadOnly" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 366} (BOOL) (I) - If TRUE, then listview is read-only
	    (defaults to FALSE).

	@{"DLV_ScrollWidth" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 361} (UWORD) (I) - Width of scroll bar for listview.
	    Must be greater than zero (defaults to 16).

	@{"DLV_ShowSelected" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 362} (void) (I) - Specify this tag to have the currently
	    selected item displayed with a highlight bar (or another method).
	    Note that this tag does not support the automatic copying to
	    a string gadget that gadtools does. You should specify ti_Data
	    as 0 for future compatibility.

	@{"DLV_Selected" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 360} (UWORD) (ISG) - Ordinal number of currently selected
	    item, or ~0 to have no current selection (defaults to ~0).

	@{"DLV_TextAttr" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 352} (struct TextAttr *) (I) - Allows you to specify a font to
	    use in the lister. Must have previously been opened.

	@{"DLV_MultiSelect" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 365} (BOOL) (I) - If TRUE, the listview allows multiple-
	    selection of items (see below for details).

	@{"DLV_Check" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 363} (BOOL) (I) - If TRUE, and @{"DLV_ShowSelected" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 362} is TRUE, the
	    current selection will be indicated with a checkmark. Note that
	    this tag has no meaning in conjunction with @{"DLV_MultiSelect" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 365}.

	@{"DLV_ShowChecks" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 368} (ULONG) (I) - If set to something other than zero,
	    checkmarks will be shown for selected items (see below for
	    details), but the user will not be able to alter their state.

	    If set to 1, selected items will be rendered in the highlight
	    pen colour. If set to 2, they will be rendered in the normal
	    text colour.

	@{"DLV_Highlight" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 364} (BOOL) (I) - If TRUE, and @{"DLV_ShowSelected" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 362} is TRUE, the
	    current selection will be displayed in a different colour.

	@{"DLV_NoScroller" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 370} (BOOL) (I) - If TRUE, the lister will not have a scroller
	    attached. The gadget will still support scrolling by "dragging"
	    the selection highlight.

	@{"DLV_TopJustify" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 371} (BOOL) (I) - If TRUE, items displayed in the lister will
	    be aligned to the top of the gadget, rather than being centred
	    vertically.

	@{"DLV_Flags" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 369} (ULONG) (I) - Allows you to specify layout flags for the lister.
	    Currently the only flags supported are :

		    PLACETEXT_ABOVE - display title above gadget (default)
		    PLACETEXT_LEFT  - display title at top-left of gadget

	@{"DLV_RightJustify" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 372} (BOOL) (I) - If TRUE, items displayed in the lister
	    will be aligned to the right of the gadget, rather than to the
	    left.

	@{"DLV_ShowFilenames" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 378} (BOOL) (I) - If TRUE, items in the lister are taken to
	    be pathnames to files, and only the filename component (ie the
	    result of a FilePart() call) is displayed. This allows you to keep
	    the full pathname in ln_Name but only display the filename.

	@{"DLV_DragNotify" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 373} (ULONG) (I) - If this is set to something other than zero,
	    the gadget will notify you when the user tries to drag an item
	    out of it. See the section on DragNotify below.

	@{"DLV_ScrollUp" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 353} (void) (S) - Use this tag with SetGadgetAttrs() to make the
	    lister scroll up one line.

	@{"DLV_ScrollDown" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 354} (void) (S) - Use this tag with SetGadgetAttrs() to make the
	    lister scroll down one line.

	@{"DLV_SelectPrevious" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 355} (void) (S) - Use this tag with SetGadgetAttrs() to make
	    the previous entry become selected.

	@{"DLV_SelectNext" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 356} (void) (S) - Use this tag with SetGadgetAttrs() to make
	    the next entry become selected.

	@{"DLV_Lines" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 367} (void) (G) - returns number of visible lines displayed in lister.

	@{"DLV_Object" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 376} (void) (G) - returns the address of the Object * structure.

	@{"DLV_GetLine" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 374} (void) (G) - this allows you to get the line number in the
	    lister from window-relative mouse coordinates. StoragePtr should be
	    initialised to the mouse coordinates ((x<<16)|y).

	@{"DLV_DrawLine" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 375} (void) (G) - this allows you to render a line of the listview
	    into your own RastPort. See the section on DragNotify below
	    for more information.

    The gadget is a subclass of gadgetclass and as such supports the
    standard gadgetclass tags (including GA_Disabled). The title of
    the gadget can be specified with GA_Text (GA_IntuiText and
    GA_LabelImage are not supported).


@{b}MULTIPLE SELECTION@{ub}

    The dopuslistviewgclass gadget supports multiple-selection of items.
    This feature is enabled by passing {@{"DLV_MultiSelect" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 365},TRUE} on creation.
    The ln_Type field of each of the node structures is used to
    indicate whether an item is selected or not. For convenience, this
    field has been renamed @{"lve_Flags" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 390}.

    To see whether an item is selected, test the @{"LVEF_SELECTED" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 392} flag in
    the @{"lve_Flags" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 390} field. Similarly, you can set an item's selection
    status by changing the value of this flag.


@{b}CUSTOM PEN COLOURS@{ub}

    You can specify the individual pen colours of each of the items in
    the list. The ln_Pri field of each of the node structures is used
    for this purpose. For convenience, this field has been renamed
    @{"lve_Pen" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 391}.

    To specify that an item is to be rendered in other than the default
    pen colour, set @{"lve_Pen" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 391} to the appropriate value and set the
    @{"LVEF_USE_PEN" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 393} flag in the @{"lve_Flags" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 390} field.


@{b}TEXT FORMATTING@{ub}

    The gadget supports simple text-formatting for item display. This
    allows you to have columns and right-justified text in the lister.

    If the text for an entry (ln_Name) contains a \\t (tab character),
    the text following that character will be right-justified in the
    lister.

    You can specify column positions using the \\a (alert) character.
    The character immediately following the \\a provides the position
    for the start of the next column. This is specified in character
    spaces. You should be aware that characters in proportional fonts
    are often wider than the nominal width of the font.

    For example, if the following items were supplied to the gadget :

	 Bloggs\\a\\xa Fred\\a\\x1a 1-Sep-65\\tPaid
	 Hall\\a\\xa Jane\\a\\x1a 9-Aug-68\\tNot paid
	 Hubbard\\a\\xa Bill\\a\\x1a 7-Mar-18\\tPaid

    The display you would see would be something like this :

	 Bloggs    Fred	    1-Sep-65	  Paid
	 Hall      Jane	    9-Aug-68      Not paid
	 Hubbard   Bill	    7-Mar-18	  Paid


@{b}DRAG NOTIFICATION@{ub}

    To enable drag notification, pass {@{"DLV_DragNotify" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 373},1} on creation.
    You will then be sent an extended taglist via the IDCMP_IDCMPUPDATE
    message when the user attempts to drag an item out of the list.
    If you pass {@{"DLV_DragNotify" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 373},2} the user will only be able to drag
    out of the list sideways; dragging up or down will scroll the list
    as usual.

    The tags you are sent on an attempted drag are as follows :

	 Tag		Data

	 GA_ID		gadget ID
	 GA_Left
	 GA_Top		window-relative item coordinates
	 GA_Width
	 GA_Height	size of the item as displayed
	 GA_RelRight
	 GA_RelBottom	offset mouse position in item
	 @{"DLV_Top" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 358}	top item number
	 @{"DLV_DragNotify" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 373}	ordinal number of item dragged

    To see if an IDCMP_IDCMPUDPATE message is from a drag, just test
    for the presence of the @{"DLV_DragNotify" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 373} tag in the taglist.

    Once you get a drag notification, the actual dragging of the item
    is your responsibility. The easiest way is using the drag routines
    provided by the dopus5.library. Create a @{"DragInfo" LINK "dopus/drag.h/File" 14} large enough for the
    item (GA_Width and GA_Height in the taglist). There are two ways to get
    the image for the bitmap.

    The first way is to use the GA_Left and GA_Top coordinates in the
    taglist and just ClipBlit() from your window into the drag rastport.
    This is the easiest way, but will also copy the checkmark if there is
    one, and you may not want that.

    The second way is to use the @{"DLV_DrawLine" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 375} tag with the GetAttr()
    call, and have the listview render the item into your bitmap for you.

    To do this, you need to initialise a @{"ListViewDraw" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 380} structure :

	 lvdraw.rp		RastPort to render into
	 lvdraw.drawinfo	DrawInfo for the screen
	 lvdraw.node		List node to render
	 lvdraw.line		Set to 0
	 lvdraw.box.Left	Set to 0
	 lvdraw.box.Top		Set to 0
	 lvdraw.box.Width	Width of BitMap
	 lvdraw.box.Height	Height of BitMap

    Then you pass the address of the @{"ListViewDraw" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 380} structure as the
    StoragePtr for the GetAttr call. Eg,

	 ULONG *ptr=(ULONG)&lvdraw;
	 Object *obj=GetTagData(@{"DLV_Object" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 376},0,tags);

	 GetAttr(@{"DLV_DrawLine" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 375},obj,&ptr);

    The GA_RelRight and GA_RelBottom tags are used to indicate where
    in the item the user clicked. When you display the drag image on
    the screen, you should offset its position by these values.


@{b}DOUBLE-CLICK NOTIFICATION@{ub}

    If you get an IDCMP_IDCMPUPDATE message from the gadget, and the
    @{"DLV_DragNotify" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 373} tag is not set, it is a normal selection message.
    An additional tag is sent in this situation; @{"DLV_DoubleClick" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 377}.
    The ti_Data field is a boolean indicating whether the selection
    is a double-click or a normal single click.

    The tags now sent for this message are :

	Tag		 Data

	GA_ID		Gadget ID
	@{"DLV_Selected" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 360}	Ordinal number of selection
	@{"DLV_DoubleClick" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 377}	BOOL


@{b}RESIZING@{ub}

    To resize the gadget, pass the new coordinates via GA_Left, GA_Top,
    GA_Width and GA_Height in a SetGadgetAttrs() call. You will then need
    to refresh the display yourself, usually by clearing the window and
    calling RefreshGList(). You may also need to call RefreshWindowFrame(),
    if the window has been resized smaller, as the gadget may have
    overwritten the window border before it was resized.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "dopuspalettegclass" "dopuspalettegclass"

@{b}dopuspalettegclass@{ub}

    The dopuspalettegclass provides a replacement for GadTools PALETTE_KIND
    gadgets. As a BOOPSI class, it allows you to have a palette gadget without
    using GadTools. This class supports the following tags:

	@{"GTCustom_TextAttr" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 295} (struct TextAttr *) (I) - used to specify a font for
	    the gadget label. (default is the window font).

	@{"GTCustom_ThinBorders" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 297} (BOOL) (I) - if set to TRUE, the gadget will be
	    rendered with single-pixel borders (default FALSE).

	GTPA_Color (UBYTE) (ISG) - the currently selected colour of the palette.
	    This number is a pen number, and not the ordinal colour number within
	    the palette gadget itself (default 1).

	GTPA_Depth (UWORD) (IS) - Number of bitplanes in the palette (default 1).

	GTPA_ColorTable (UBYTE *) (IS) - Pointer to a table of pen numbers
	    indicating which colours should be used and edited by the palette
	    gadget. This array must contain as many entries as there are colours
	    displayed in the palette gadget. The array provided with this tag
	    must remain valid for the life of the gadget, or until a new table
	    is provided. (default is NULL, which causes a 1-to-1 mapping of pen
	    numbers).

	GTPA_NumColors (UWORD) (IS) - Number of colours to display in the palette
	    gadget. This overrides GTPA_Depth and allows numbers which aren't
	    powers of 2. (defaults to 2)

	@{"DPG_Pen" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 400} (UWORD) (ISG) - the currently selected colour of the palette.
	    This is similar to GTPA_Color but refers to the ordinal colour
	    number and not the pen number itself.

	@{"DPG_SelectNext" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 402} (void) (S) - use this tag with SetGadgetAttrs() to cause
	    the next colour in the gadget to be selected.

	@{"DPG_SelectPrevious" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 401} (void) (S) - use this tag with SetGadgetAttrs() to
	    cause the previous colour in the gadget to be selected.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "dopusstrgclass" "dopusstrgclass"

@{b}dopusstrgclass@{ub}

    This dopusstrgclass provides a replacement for GadTools STRING_KIND
    gadgets. It is basically a standard string gadget with an automatic
    border, but also supports additional features. This class is based
    on the dopusbuttongclass, and as such supports all the tags of that
    class. It is also a subclass of strgclass and supports the standard
    string gadget tags of that class (with some important changes, listed
    below). The control tags supported by this class are as follows:

	STRINGA_Buffer (char *) (I) - Specify the main buffer for the gadget.
	    If this is not supplied, a buffer will be allocated automatically
	    (this does not suffer from the maximum 128 bytes limitation of the
	    standard BOOPSI string gadget class).

	STRINGA_UndoBuffer (char *) (I) - Specify the undo buffer for the
	    gadget. Again, one will be allocated automatically if you do not
	    supply one.

	STRINGA_WorkBuffer (char *) (I) - Specify the work buffer for the
	    gadget. This will also be automatically allocated if you do not
	    supply it.

	STRINGA_MaxChars (long) (I) - Specify the maximum length of the string
	    editable by this gadget. If buffers are allocated automatically,
	    they will be this size. GTST_MaxChars and GTIN_MaxChars are also
	    synonyms for this tag. (defaults to 40).

	STRINGA_Font (struct TextFont *) (I) - Specify the font to use for this
	    gadget.

	@{"GTCustom_ChangeSigTask" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 313} (struct Task *) (I) - Specify a task that is to
	    be signalled whenever the contents of this gadget change.
	    (defaults to NULL).

	@{"GTCustom_ChangeSigBit" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 314} (BYTE) (I) - Specify the signal bit that is used
	    to signal a task whenever the contents of this gadget change.
	    (defaults to 0).

	STRINGA_TextVal (char *) (IS) - Set the contents of the string gadget.
	    The supplied string is copied to the buffer. GTST_String, GTTX_Text,
	    GTIN_Number and GTNM_Number are valid synonyms for this tag.

    To use the dopus5.library edit hook with a string gadget, you should
    call @{"GetEditHook()" LINK "GetEditHook"} and pass the results with the STRINGA_EditHook tag.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "dopusviewgclass" "dopusviewgclass"

@{b}dopusviewgclass@{ub}

    This class provides a simple view gadget, similar to GadTools TEXT_KIND
    and NUMBER_KIND gadgets. It is a subclass of dopusbuttongclass, and so
    supports all the tags of that class. To set the contents of the view
    gadget, use the GTTX_Text or GTNM_Number tags (a view gadget can be
    used to display either text or a number interchangeably).

