	parsed part of the input string. If the range returns @{"RANGE_BETWEEN" LINK "dopus/dos.h/File" 29}
	(to signify a range between two dates), you will need to call
	ParseDateStrings() again on the remainder of the string to get the
	next date and time.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"DateFromStrings()" LINK "DateFromStrings"}

