@NODE "Edit_Hook" "Edit_Hook"
@{b}Edit Hook@{ub}

	@{"FreeEditHook()   " LINK "FreeEditHook"}
	@{"GetEditHook()    " LINK "GetEditHook"}
	@{"GetSecureString()" LINK "GetSecureString"}


@{b}PURPOSE@{ub}

    The dopus5.library provides an edit hook which you can attach to string
    gadgets, to take advantage of some additional features. The features
    provided by the edit hook include :

	- Enhanced cursor movement using alt and shift
	- History using up/down cursor
	- Clipboard support (copy, cut and paste)
	- Optional filtering of path characters
	- Secure option where string is not displayed
	- Return automatically activates the next string gadget
	- Key press notification

    To use the edit hook in your gadgets, you must obtain a Hook structure
    with the @{"GetEditHook()" LINK "GetEditHook"} function. Once you have finished with it, you
    must free this with @{"FreeEditHook()" LINK "FreeEditHook"}.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "FreeEditHook" "FreeEditHook()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	FreeEditHook - free a Hook created with @{"GetEditHook()" LINK "GetEditHook"}@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	FreeEditHook(hook)
		      A0

	void FreeEditHook(struct Hook *);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	This routine frees a Hook that you obtained via a call to
	@{"GetEditHook()" LINK "GetEditHook"}.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	hook - hook to free@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"GetEditHook()" LINK "GetEditHook"}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "GetEditHook" "GetEditHook()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	GetEditHook - get a Hook pointer to access the edit hook@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	GetEditHook(type, flags, tags)
		     D0     D1    A0

	struct Hook *GetEditHook(ULONG, ULONG, struct TagItem *);

	struct Hook *GetEditHookTags(ULONG, ULONG, Tag, ...);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	This routine returns a Hook structure that you can use to give
	the additional capabilities to your string gadgets.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	type - type of Hook (only @{"HOOKTYPE_STANDARD" LINK "dopus/edithook.h/File" 14} is valid so far)
	flags - a combination of the following flags :

		@{"EDITF_NO_SELECT_NEXT" LINK "dopus/edithook.h/File" 10} - stops the return key from
		automatically activating the next (or previous, with shift)
		string gadget.

		@{"EDITF_PATH_FILTER" LINK "dopus/edithook.h/File" 11} - filters path characters out of the
		string (/ and :)

		@{"EDITF_SECURE" LINK "dopus/edithook.h/File" 12} - secure password field, doesn't display the
		characters that are typed. If this flag is specified, the
		gadget's StringInfo->MaxChars value must be twice what
		it would ordinarily be. The gadget's StringInfo->Buffer
		must be this size plus an additional two bytes, eg
		(max_len*2)+2.

	tags - the following tags are supported by the edit hook :

	       @{"EH_History" LINK "dopus/edithook.h/File" 16} - supplies a pointer to an @{"Att_List" LINK "dopus/lists.h/File" 10} structure
	       which contains the history list for this gadget. Each entry
	       in the list is the name of a node, with the most recent node
	       at the end of the list. The @{"Att_List" LINK "dopus/lists.h/File" 10} should be created using
	       Semaphore locking.

	       @{"EH_ChangeSigTask" LINK "dopus/edithook.h/File" 17} - allows you to specify a task that is to be
	       signalled whenever the contents of the string gadget are
	       changed by the user. This allows you to have a display
	       dynamically updated as the user types.

	       @{"EH_ChangeSigBit" LINK "dopus/edithook.h/File" 18} - the signal bit used to signal your task.
	       This is the bit number, not a mask.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
	Returns a pointer to a Hook structure which you can use for your
	gadget. It is not a good idea to share hooks between gadgets
	(although unless you are using the @{"EH_History" LINK "dopus/edithook.h/File" 16} facility it should
	not really be a problem).@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"FreeEditHook()" LINK "FreeEditHook"}, @{"GetSecureString()" LINK "GetSecureString"}, @{"Att_NewList()" LINK "Att_NewList"}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "GetSecureString" "GetSecureString()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	GetSecureString - retrieve the real string from a secure field@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	GetSecureString(gadget)
			  A0

	char *GetSecureString(struct Gadget *);@{b}

