@NODE "IFFNextChunk" "IFFNextChunk()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	IFFNextChunk - skip to the next chunk@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	IFFNextChunk(handle, chunkid)
		       A0       D0

	ULONG IFFNextChunk(APTR, ULONG);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	This is the main work-horse of the IFF routines. This function will
	scan through the IFF file from the current position looking for the
	next chunk. You can optionally specify a chunk to look for.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	handle - IFF handle
	chunkid - ID of chunk to look for, or 0 for next chunk@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
	Returns ID of the new chunk, or 0 for error or end-of-file.@{b}

    NOTES@{ub}
	The IFF routines do not handle LISTs, CATs or other complicated IFF
	structures. This routine will handle multiple FORMs within the one
	file, which allows it to read ANIMs.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"IFFOpen()" LINK "IFFOpen"}, @{"IFFReadChunkBytes()" LINK "IFFReadChunkBytes"}

