	In addition to these tags, @{"OPUS_LISTVIEW_KIND" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 343} gadgets (via the Opus
	BOOPSI listview class) supports several additional tags. See the
	section on the listview class for information on these.


    The last member in an array of @{"ObjectDef" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 74} structures must have a od_Type
    of @{"OD_END" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 115} set.


    3.  The layout routines can only add gadgets to a special sort of window;
    one that has been created with the @{"OpenConfigWindow()" LINK "OpenConfigWindow"} call. Two structures
    are needed to open one of these windows. The first, a @{"ConfigWindow" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 30} structure,
    specifies the position and size of the new window. It has cw_CharDims and
    cw_FineDims fields, analogous to the fields in @{"ObjectDef" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 74} structures.

    The second is a @{"NewConfigWindow" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 36} structure. This is initialised as follows:

	nw_Parent

	This field points to the parent of the Window. The parent can be
	either another window (the default) or a screen (if the
	WINDOWF_SCREEN_PARENT flag is set).


	nw_Dims

	This points to the @{"ConfigWindow" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 30} structure used to define the size
	of the new window.


	nw_Title

	This points to a title string for the new window.


	nw_Locale

	This points to a valid DOpusLocale structure for the window. All
	ObjectDefs that use a locale ID will obtain their strings via this
	structure.


	nw_Port

	Allows you to specify a message port to use; you should set this to
	NULL.


	nw_Flags

	Control flags. Valid values are:

	    @{"WINDOW_SCREEN_PARENT" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 47}    - nw_Parent points to a Screen
	    @{"WINDOW_NO_CLOSE" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 48}	 - no close gadget on the window
	    @{"WINDOW_NO_BORDER" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 49}	- borderless window
	    @{"WINDOW_SIMPLE" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 51}	   - simplerefresh window
	    @{"WINDOW_AUTO_REFRESH" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 52}     - use with @{"WINDOW_SIMPLE" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 51}
	    @{"WINDOW_AUTO_KEYS" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 53}	- handle keypresses automatically
	    @{"WINDOW_REQ_FILL" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 55}	 - backfill the window with stipple pattern
	    @{"WINDOW_NO_ACTIVATE" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 56}      - don't activate the window on open
	    @{"WINDOW_VISITOR" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 57}	  - open as a visitor window
	    @{"WINDOW_SIZE_RIGHT" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 58}       - size gadget in right border
	    @{"WINDOW_SIZE_BOTTOM" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 59}      - size gadget in bottom border
	    @{"WINDOW_ICONIFY" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 60}	  - iconify gadget in title bar


	nw_Font

	Allows you to specify a font to use for the window. If NULL, the
	current screen font will be used.

