@NODE "AddWindowMenus" "AddWindowMenus()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	AddWindowMenus - add menus to a window@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	AddWindowMenus(window, menus)
			 A0     A1

	void AddWindowMenus(struct Window *, @{"MenuData" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 198} *);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	This function makes it easy to add menus to a window opened via
	@{"OpenConfigWindow()" LINK "OpenConfigWindow"}. Even if you don't use the @{"AddObjectList()" LINK "AddObjectList"} routine
	to add gadgets to the window, you can still use this call to add
	menus.

	AddWindowMenus() takes an array of @{"MenuData" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 198} structures, and constructs
	and initialises the Intuition Menu structures automatically. The
	@{"MenuData" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 198} structures are initialised as follows:

	    md_Type     - entry type; NM_TITLE, NM_ITEM or NM_SUB. The array
			  must be terminated by an NM_END item.

	    md_ID       - the ID value for the menu item.

	    md_Name     - the name of the menu item. This can either be a
			  locale ID, or, if the @{"MENUFLAG_TEXT_STRING" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 205} flag is
			  set, a pointer to a real string.

	    md_Flags    - control flags.

	The md_Flags field supports the standard Intuition and GadTools menu
	flags as well as several custom flags:

	    @{"MENUFLAG_TEXT_STRING" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 205} - md_Name is a real string
	    @{"MENUFLAG_COMM_SEQ" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 206}    - the menu will be given a command sequence
				   (Right-Amiga + a key)
	    @{"MENUFLAG_AUTO_MUTEX" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 207}  - automatic mutual exclusion

	If @{"MENUFLAG_COMM_SEQ" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 206} is specified, the key used for the command
	sequence is normally the first character of the menu name. However,
	you can specify a character to use instead of this, by setting the
	@{"MENUFLAG_USE_SEQ" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 208} flag, and using the @{"MENUFLAG_MAKE_SEQ" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 210}() macro.
	For example, to specify a command sequence of Right Amiga and A, you
	would use :

	    @{"MENUFLAG_COMM_SEQ" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 206}|@{"MENUFLAG_USE_SEQ" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 208}|@{"MENUFLAG_MAKE_SEQ" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 210}('A')

	The automatic mutual exclusion works on all items at the current
	level that have the CHECKIT flag set.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	window - window to add menus to
	menus - array of @{"MenuData" LINK "dopus/layout.h/File" 198} structures, terminated with NM_END@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
	The menus are added to the window. You can check if this operation
	failed (through lack of memory) by examining the window->MenuStrip
	pointer; if NULL, the window has no menus.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"FindMenuItem()" LINK "FindMenuItem"}, @{"FreeWindowMenus()" LINK "FreeWindowMenus"}

@ENDNODE
