@NODE "AddNotifyRequest" "AddNotifyRequest()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	AddNotifyRequest - add a request to Opus's notify chain@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	AddNotifyRequest(type, userdata, port)
			  D0      D1      A0

	APTR AddNotifyRequest(ULONG, ULONG, struct MsgPort *);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	Opus keeps track of several different system events, and this routine
	allows you to request notification on them.

	The events currently available for notification:

	    @{"DN_WRITE_ICON" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 26}      - an icon is written to disk
	    @{"DN_APP_ICON_LIST" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 27}   - an AppIcon is added or removed
	    @{"DN_APP_MENU_LIST" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 28}   - an AppMenuItem is added or removed
	    @{"DN_CLOSE_WORKBENCH" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 29} - CloseWorkbench() has been called
	    @{"DN_OPEN_WORKBENCH" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 30}  - OpenWorkbench() has been called
	    @{"DN_RESET_WORKBENCH" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 31} - the workbench screen has been closed and
				 re-opened
	    @{"DN_DISKCHANGE" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 32}      - a disk has been inserted or removed
	    @{"DN_DOS_ACTION" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 37}      - a DOS event has occurred. In Opus 5.5,
				 these messages are only available if the
				 dopus/DOSPatch environment variable is set.
	    @{"DN_REXX_UP" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 38}	 - the ARexx process has been started.

	Several Opus events are also available for notification:

	    @{"DN_OPUS_START" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 36}      - Opus has started
	    @{"DN_OPUS_QUIT" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 33}       - Opus has quit
	    @{"DN_OPUS_HIDE" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 34}       - Opus has been hidden
	    @{"DN_OPUS_SHOW" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 35}       - Opus has been revealed

	When an event occurs that you have requested notification for, a
	@{"DOpusNotify" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 11} message is sent to your message port. The message
	structure is defined as follows:

	    dn_Msg      - Exec message header

	    dn_Type     - Event type

	    dn_UserData - the userdata you supplied to AddNotifyRequest()

	    dn_Data     - data specific to the type of event

	    dn_Flags    - flags specific to the type of event

	    dn_Fib      - a FileInfoBlock for some types of event

	    dn_Name     - pathname specific to the type of event


	The event-specific fields are used in the following way:

	    @{"DN_WRITE_ICON" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 26}
	    -------------
		dn_Data  - NULL
		dn_Flags - if @{"DNF_ICON_REMOVED" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 41} is set, icon was deleted
		dn_Fib   - NULL
		dn_Name  - full pathname of icon

	    @{"DN_APP_ICON_LIST" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 27}
	    ----------------
		dn_Data  - pointer to the AppIcon added or removed
		dn_Flags - if @{"DNF_ICON_REMOVED" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 41} is set, icon was removed
			   if @{"DNF_ICON_CHANGED" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 42} is set, the icon image
			   was changed
		dn_Fib   - NULL
		dn_Name  - NULL

	    @{"DN_APP_MENU_LIST" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 28}
	    ----------------
		dn_Data  - pointer to the AppMenuItem added or removed
		dn_Flags - if @{"DNF_ICON_REMOVED" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 41} is set, item was removed
		dn_Fib   - NULL
		dn_Name  - NULL

	    @{"DN_DISKCHANGE" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 32}
	    -------------
		dn_Data  - disk units the change occurred in (bits 0-3
			   represent units 0-3)
		dn_Flags - which units have disks in them (bits 0-3
			   represent units 0-3)
		dn_Fib   - NULL
		dn_Name  - NULL

	    @{"DN_DOS_ACTION" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File" 37}
	    -------------
		dn_Data  - NULL
		dn_Flags - which DOS action occurred (see <@{"dopus/notify.h" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File"}>)
		dn_Fib   - FileInfoBlock with file information. This is
			   supplied for all actions except Delete.
		dn_Name  - full pathname of file involved@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	type - type of events you want to be notified of. One request can
	       ask for multiple events. See <@{"dopus/notify.h" LINK "dopus/notify.h/File"}> for the full
	       list.

	userdata - a user-defined data field that is passed in any notify
		   messages.

	port - message port to send notification messages to.@{b}

    NOTES@{ub}
	Most notification messages are sent "reply free", meaning you must
	use the @{"ReplyFreeMsg()" LINK "ReplyFreeMsg"} call to reply to them. Otherwise, the
	message memory will be lost.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
	Returns a notify handle which you use to remove the request.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"RemoveNotifyRequest()" LINK "RemoveNotifyRequest"}, @{"SetNotifyRequest()" LINK "SetNotifyRequest"}

@ENDNODE
