    NAME@{ub}
	OpenProgressWindow - open a progress window display@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	OpenProgressWindow(tags)
			    A0

	APTR OpenProgressWindow(struct TagItem *);

	APTR OpenProgressWindowTags(Tag, ...);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	Opens a progress window that your application can use to display the
	progression of some operation. The progress window can have a filename
	display, file counter and progress gauge.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	tags - control tags. Control tags are:

	    @{"PW_Screen" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 14}    - screen to open on. The progress window will
			   appear centred in the screen. Use of this tag
			   overrides @{"PW_Window" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 15}.

	    @{"PW_Window" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 15}    - window to open over. The progress window will
			   appear centred over the supplied window.

	    @{"PW_Title" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 16}     - title for the progress window

	    @{"PW_SigTask" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 17}   - task to signal when the abort gadget is pressed.

	    @{"PW_SigBit" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 18}    - bit to signal task with (signal bit, not mask)

	    @{"PW_FileName" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 20}  - initial filename for display

	    @{"PW_FileSize" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 21}  - initial file size

	    @{"PW_FileCount" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 23} - initial file count

	    @{"PW_Flags" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 19}     - control flags

	The control flags for the @{"PW_Flags" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 19} tag are :

	    @{"PWF_FILENAME" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 27}  - specify if you want a filename display
	    @{"PWF_FILESIZE" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 28}  - specify if you want a file size display (1)
	    @{"PWF_INFO" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 29}      - specify if you want an information line
	    @{"PWF_GRAPH" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 30}     - specify if you want a bar graph display (1)
	    @{"PWF_NOABORT" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 31}   - specify if you don't want an Abort button (2)
	    @{"PWF_INVISIBLE" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 32} - if you want the progress window to open in 'hidden'
			    mode (ie you need to call @{"ShowProgressWindow()" LINK "ShowProgressWindow"} to
			    make it visible)
	    @{"PWF_ABORT" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 33}     - specify if you do want an Abort button (2)

	1. Ordinarily, the file size is displayed as a "xxxxxx bytes" string in
	   the top-right of the progress window, and the bar graph is used to
	   represent "x out of y files". If, however, you specify both
	   @{"PWF_FILESIZE" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 28} and @{"PWF_GRAPH" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 30}, the meanings of these displays is
	   automatically swapped around. The current file progress (eg bytes
	   copied) is displayed in the bar graph, and the current operation
	   progress (eg files copied) is displayed in text in the top-right
	   corner.

	2. If you specify a signal task with the pw_SigTask flag, the
	   progress window will automatically get an Abort button. You can use
	   the @{"PWF_NOABORT" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 31} flag to stop this happening.

	   If you do not specify the pw_SigTask flag, you can use the @{"PWF_ABORT" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 33}
	   flag to add an Abort button without signalling (you will need to
	   call @{"CheckProgressAbort()" LINK "CheckProgressAbort"} to detect an abort).@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
	Returns a handle to the newly created progress window, or NULL for
	failure.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"SetProgressWindow()" LINK "SetProgressWindow"}, @{"CloseProgressWindow()" LINK "CloseProgressWindow"}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetProgressWindow" "SetProgressWindow()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
	SetProgressWindow - update progress window information@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	SetProgressWindow(handle, tags)
			    A0     A1

	void SetProgressWindow(APTR, struct TagItem *);

	void SetProgressWindowTags(APTR, Tag, ...);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
	This is the routine you use to update the information displayed in
	a progress window.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
	handle - progress window handle
	tags   - control tags. Valid tags are :

	    @{"PW_Title" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 16}       - change the window title

	    @{"PW_FileName" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 20}    - change the displayed filename

	    @{"PW_FileSize" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 21}    - change the total size of the current file

	    @{"PW_FileDone" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 22}    - change the "done" size of the current file
			     (eg, if the file size was 12800 and you had
			     copied half of it, the done size would be
			     6400).

	    @{"PW_Info" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 25}	- change the information field display

	    @{"PW_FileCount" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 23}   - change the total number of files

	    @{"PW_FileNum" LINK "dopus/progress.h/File" 24}     - change the number of files processed (eg,
			     if the total file count was 84 and you had
			     processed a quarter of them, the current
			     file number would be 21).@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
	The changes are displayed immediately. If the progress window is
	currently hidden, the changes are still effective and will be
	visible when the progress window is revealed.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"OpenProgressWindow()" LINK "OpenProgressWindow"}

